Relationship between of blood flow, glucose metabolism, protein synthesis, glucose and ATP content in experimentally - induced glioma ( RG1 2. 2) of rat brain.

In experimental RG1 2. 2 glioma of rat brain, local blood flow, glucose utilization, protein synthesis, glucose and ATP content were measured by means of triple tracer autoradiography and bioluminescence technique, respectively, to determine hemodynamic and metabolic thresholds for local tumor energy failure.

Metabolic thresholds were derived at tumor glucose utilization values of 70. 6 + / - 8. 3 mumol / 100 g / min for reduced protein synthesis, of 55. 0 + / - 0. 2 mumol / 100 g / min for the decrease in glucose content, and 34. 7 + / - 4. 7 mumol / 100 g / min for decline in ATP content.
